      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "The Conditional",
        "content": "The conditional expresses what WOULD happen. Like future, add endings to the infinitive:\n                              → -ían = ellos/Uds.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "-ía",
            "english": "yo"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-ías",
            "english": "tú"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-ía",
            "english": "él/ella/Ud."
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-íamos",
            "english": "nosotros"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-ían",
            "english": "ellos/Uds."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Examples: HABLAR",
        "content": "Infinitive + conditional endings:\n                              \n   ✏️ Exercise: Yo ___ más si tuviera tiempo. (estudiar)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "hablaría",
            "english": "I would speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hablarías",
            "english": "you would speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hablaría",
            "english": "he/she would speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hablaríamos",
            "english": "we would speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hablarían",
            "english": "they would speak"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Irregular Conditionals",
        "content": "Same irregular stems as future:\n                              \n   ✏️ Exercise: ¿Qué ___ tú en mi situación? (hacer)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "tener → tendría",
            "english": "would have"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "poder → podría",
            "english": "would be able"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "hacer → haría",
            "english": "would do/make"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "decir → diría",
            "english": "would say"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "querer → querría",
            "english": "would want"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Uses of Conditional",
        "content": "Common uses:\n                        \n   ✏️ Exercise: Translate: 'I would like to travel to Spain'\n\n   ✏️ Exercise: Polite: 'Could you repeat, please?'",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Me gustaría un café",
            "english": "I would like a coffee (polite)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "¿Podrías ayudarme?",
            "english": "Could you help me? (polite)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Yo compraría esa casa",
            "english": "I would buy that house (hypothetical)"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Dijo que vendría",
            "english": "He said he would come (reported speech)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
